# Studying Candidate Antitumor Cell Activity with the Airalogy Protocol

## Overview

This protocol uses a common biomedical dose-response cell viability assay as an example. It shows how the Airalogy Protocol connects experimental design, raw data upload, automatic calculation, visualization, and report generation into a reusable research workflow.

Example scenario: evaluating the in vitro activity of a candidate antitumor small molecule in a tumor cell model. After the researcher uploads CCK-8 cell viability readout data, the protocol automatically calculates normalized cell viability, estimates IC50, plots the dose-response curve, performs quality control, and generates a structured experimental report.

