## Data Upload

Please upload dose-response assay data in CSV format:

{{var|dose_response_file: FileIdCSV}}

<details>
<summary>CSV format requirements and example</summary>

The CSV must contain these columns:

| concentration_um | signal_mean | signal_sd | n |
|-----------------:|------------:|----------:|--:|
| 0.001            | 98000       | 2600      | 3 |
| 0.003            | 95500       | 2400      | 3 |
| 0.01             | 90000       | 2500      | 3 |
| ...              | ...         | ...       | ... |

Field notes:

- `concentration_um`: candidate compound concentration in μM; must be greater than 0.
- `signal_mean`: mean readout for the dose group, such as absorbance, fluorescence, or luminescence.
- `signal_sd`: standard deviation of readouts in the dose group; optional but recommended for QC and error bars.
- `n`: number of replicate wells; optional.

</details>

## Auto-Computed Results

Number of dose points: {{var|point_count: int}}
Minimum normalized cell viability (%): {{var|min_viability_pct: float}}
Maximum inhibition (%): {{var|max_inhibition_pct: float}}
Estimated IC50 (μM): {{var|ic50_um: float}}
log10(IC50): {{var|log_ic50: float}}
IC50 within tested concentration range: {{var|ic50_in_range: bool}}
Mean log-dose inhibition AUC (%): {{var|auc_inhibition: float}}
Maximum replicate CV (%): {{var|max_cv_pct: float}}
QC pass: {{var|qc_pass: bool}}

<details>
<summary>QC criteria</summary>

QC passes when all of the following conditions are met:

- At least 6 valid dose points are present.
- The vehicle control signal is greater than the blank well signal.
- The dose-response curve crosses 50% cell viability, so IC50 can be estimated within the tested concentration range.
- If `signal_sd` is provided, the maximum replicate CV is not greater than 20%.

</details>

